Project: Automated Fact-Checker for Vernacular News

Live Links:
•	https://ghoshsayan000.github.io/fact-checker/frontend/index.html
________________________________________

What it does: Takes any news or social media post in any Indian language (Hindi, Tamil, Bengali, etc.), fact-checks it against live web sources, and returns a verdict of True, False, or Unverified with confidence score, explanation, and sources.
________________________________________

Tech Stack:
•	Frontend: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
•	Backend: Python, FastAPI
•	AI Model: Google Gemini (gemini-3-flash-preview)
•	Web Search: SerpAPI
•	Web Scraping: BeautifulSoup4
•	Deployment: Render.com (backend), GitHub Pages (frontend)

________________________________________

The 5 Step Pipeline:
Step 1 - Optimizer: Takes raw vernacular text, translates it to English using Gemini AI and extracts the single core factual claim. This is the required Pipeline Optimization technique — it strips all conversational fluff before any expensive processing happens, ensuring high throughput.
Step 2 - Key Term Extractor: Gemini AI reads the clean claim and identifies key terms, context, and generates 2-3 targeted search queries for web verification.
Step 3 - Web Search and Scrape: SerpAPI searches Google for each query and returns top results. BeautifulSoup4 scrapes the actual page content from each result for deeper analysis.
Step 4 - Evidence Summarizer: Gemini AI reads all scraped web content and compresses it into structured evidence — summary, supporting sources, contradicting sources, and key facts.
Step 5 - Verdict Engine: Gemini AI reasons over the summarized evidence and delivers a final verdict of True, False, or Unverified with confidence percentage, explanation, and source URLs.

________________________________________

Why this is better than Google Fact Check API: The Google Fact Check API only checks claims already in its database — covering maybe 1% of Indian vernacular misinformation.
Our pipeline searches the live web, meaning it can fact-check any claim including breaking news, regional news, and claims that have never been checked before.
It also provides AI reasoning and explanation, not just a database lookup.

________________________________________

How the Required Technique is implemented: The project requirement specifically asked for Pipeline Optimization. 
This is implemented in Step 1 (step1_optimizer.py) where Gemini AI strips all conversational filler, emojis, hashtags, and irrelevant content from the raw post before any web search or analysis happens.
This means the expensive steps (web search, scraping, AI analysis) only process clean, relevant factual claims — dramatically improving throughput and accuracy.

